questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Read the given statements and conclusions carefully. Assuming that the information given in the statements is true, even if it appears to be at variance with commonly known facts, decide which of the given conclusions logically follow(s) from the statements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) No movie is a song.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) All songs are anthems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. All movies being anthems is a possibility.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. All songs can never be movies.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;According to the given statements we have&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/23/05/F2_Engineering_Savita_28-4-23_D36.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 253px; height: 91px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;I. All movies being anthems is a possibility.&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; Follow: Since no movie is a song and all song is anthems. So, all movie being anthem is possible. This is true.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;II. All songs can never be movies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;rarr; Follow: Since it is given no movie is a song. So all songs are movie is not possible. This it is true.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, &lt;strong&gt;both conclusions follow&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;option (3)&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given that,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Total people in row = 25&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Keshav is&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;from the extreme right end.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Teja sits 5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;to the left of Keshav.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, Teja&amp;#39;s position from the right end = 7 + 5 = 12&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Now, Teja&amp;#39;s position from the left end = Total people - Teja&amp;#39;s position from the right end + 1 = 25 - 12 + 1 = 14&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​The diagram is given below-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/05/Pic188.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 600px; height: 183px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;option 1&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is the correct answer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Flow&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;Stagnant&amp;#39; are &lt;strong&gt;antonyms &lt;/strong&gt;in the context that flow refers to movement and stagnation refers to a lack of movement.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Following this pattern, we would need an &lt;strong&gt;antonym&lt;/strong&gt; for &amp;#39;Fall.&amp;#39;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In that context, &amp;#39;Fall&amp;#39; would be synonymous with decline or dropping, and its antonym would be &amp;#39;Rise&amp;#39;, or increasing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, &amp;#39;Flow&amp;#39; is related to &amp;#39;Stagnant&amp;#39; in the same way &amp;#39;Fall&amp;#39; is related to &amp;#39;Rise&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the correct answer is 1) Rise.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;If the following words are arranged as per their order in the English dictionary, which word will come fifth in the sequence?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Weekly&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. Weather&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3. Weird&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4. Weaver&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;5. Weight&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;6. Wielded&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;Weather comes first in the order.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is followed by Weaver.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Weaver is followed by Weekly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Weekly is followed by Weight.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Weight is followed by Weird.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Weird is followed by Wielded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct dictionary order is,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Weather (2) &amp;rarr; Weaver (4) &amp;rarr; Weekly (1) &amp;rarr; Weight (5) &amp;rarr; Weird (3) &amp;rarr; Wielded (6)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Weird comes fifth in the order.&lt;/p&gt;
Hence, &amp;ldquo;weird&amp;rdquo; is the correct answer.

&lt;p&gt;According to the English alphabet series and its positional value:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/21/05/Common_Diagram_28.01.2020_D1.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 536px; height: 128px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The pattern followed here is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pattern: Product of the place value of the given letters.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FAT &amp;rarr;&amp;nbsp;6&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 1 &amp;times; 20 = 120&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NOD &amp;rarr;&amp;nbsp;14 &amp;times; 15 &amp;times; 4&amp;nbsp;= 840,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the same manner&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;DAY &amp;rarr;&amp;nbsp;4&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 1 &amp;times; 25&amp;nbsp;= 100.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, DAY&amp;nbsp;is written as&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;100&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Checking all the options,&lt;/p&gt;

